<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-08-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-08-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2300/1: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-30T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 30,
                                        1923—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>102. Refer to Department’s mail instruction of July 18 in regard proposed
                            air flight around the world.</p>
                        <p>You will advise Department by cable whether proposed flight over Japanese
                            territory could be arranged for under present law, and whether request
                            could, in your judgment, be made without antagonizing Japanese opinion,
                            both official and popular.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>